1
00:01:31,120 --> 00:01:35,950
[Life is a Choice]

2
00:01:37,050 --> 00:01:39,210
President Feng is really good at sailing under false colors.

3
00:01:38,870 --> 00:01:40,830
[Episode 12]

4
00:01:39,630 --> 00:01:41,380
How sanctimonious.

5
00:01:41,250 --> 00:01:43,270
[It's just a breakup]

6
00:01:42,000 --> 00:01:43,390
Really admirable.

7
00:01:46,270 --> 00:01:49,000
There were some small mistakes in the setup.

8
00:01:49,100 --> 00:01:49,990
Let's coordinate.

9
00:01:50,030 --> 00:01:50,770
Please, everyone, stay calm.

10
00:01:53,170 --> 00:01:53,810
Su Yin,

11
00:01:54,280 --> 00:01:56,440
there should be limits to your recklessness!

12
00:01:56,720 --> 00:01:57,850
Where are we?

13
00:01:58,229 --> 00:01:59,580
I'm asking you, where are we?

14
00:02:01,770 --> 00:02:02,770
Ladies and gentlemen,

15
00:02:03,030 --> 00:02:05,690
this is the big talent from our Economics department.

16
00:02:06,260 --> 00:02:07,190
For the past two years,

17
00:02:07,820 --> 00:02:09,660
under the pretext of helping left-behind children in his hometown,

18
00:02:09,830 --> 00:02:10,990
he has "donated" all the money

19
00:02:11,590 --> 00:02:12,980
to his own family.

20
00:02:13,790 --> 00:02:15,230
While gaining a good reputation,

21
00:02:15,620 --> 00:02:16,870
he also managed to make himself rich.

22
00:02:17,310 --> 00:02:18,460
He really knows how to scheme.

23
00:02:20,630 --> 00:02:22,540
Don't slander me.

24
00:02:22,810 --> 00:02:26,180
Guo Yongcheng, sponsored by the drama club, is a left-behind child.

25
00:02:26,650 --> 00:02:28,220
What does that have to do with me?

26
00:02:28,460 --> 00:02:29,820
Am I slandering you?

27
00:02:30,050 --> 00:02:31,440
Guo Yongcheng has nothing to do with you?

28
00:02:32,020 --> 00:02:33,620
What about his older sister, Guo Yongfang?

29
00:02:33,980 --> 00:02:35,030
Does she have nothing to do with you either?

30
00:02:37,579 --> 00:02:38,610
Are you not willing to answer,

31
00:02:39,260 --> 00:02:40,430
or just afraid to answer?

32
00:02:43,020 --> 00:02:45,220
So, every time he sends money to Guo Yongcheng,

33
00:02:45,220 --> 00:02:46,660
you transfer it back to his mother, right?

34
00:02:46,910 --> 00:02:49,670
Well, his mother is basically also mine.

35
00:02:50,230 --> 00:02:51,890
We grew up together.

36
00:02:52,380 --> 00:02:54,020
When he finishes university and comes back,

37
00:02:54,720 --> 00:02:55,950
we'll get married.

38
00:02:56,460 --> 00:02:58,180
He's saving up for our dowry.

39
00:02:59,070 --> 00:03:00,440
I give the money to Auntie Feng

40
00:03:00,660 --> 00:03:02,460
to show respect to my future mother-in-law.

41
00:03:02,970 --> 00:03:05,090
Guo Yongfang is your fiancée back in your hometown.

42
00:03:05,630 --> 00:03:07,420
Every penny you send to Guo Yongcheng

43
00:03:07,450 --> 00:03:08,810
is transferred to your mom through Guo Yongfang

44
00:03:09,340 --> 00:03:09,910
Because she knows

45
00:03:09,910 --> 00:03:11,300
you two are going to be family sooner or later.

46
00:03:11,690 --> 00:03:13,140
How would I know

47
00:03:13,140 --> 00:03:14,430
she transferred the money to my mom?

48
00:03:14,620 --> 00:03:15,900
I was just reasonably and lawfully

49
00:03:16,030 --> 00:03:17,790
sending money to her.

50
00:03:18,220 --> 00:03:20,710
Because she is Guo Yongcheng's only guardian.

51
00:03:20,970 --> 00:03:21,700
What's wrong with that?

52
00:03:22,060 --> 00:03:22,820
So, you admit

53
00:03:22,820 --> 00:03:23,990
your relationship with her, then?

54
00:03:24,790 --> 00:03:26,020
In such a large place,

55
00:03:26,660 --> 00:03:28,420
with so many left-behind children eligible,

56
00:03:28,420 --> 00:03:30,220
why did you choose Guo Yongcheng?

57
00:03:31,360 --> 00:03:32,750
Could it really be a coincidence?

58
00:03:41,880 --> 00:03:43,000
I'm really sorry.

59
00:03:43,030 --> 00:03:44,190
I didn't expect this to happen.

60
00:03:48,660 --> 00:03:49,820
What kind of person is this?

61
00:03:54,980 --> 00:03:56,829
Su Yin, don't go too far.

62
00:03:56,850 --> 00:03:58,890
What exactly are you trying to do?

63
00:03:59,180 --> 00:03:59,940
Feng Huanan,

64
00:04:00,580 --> 00:04:01,510
go ahead, hit me.

65
00:04:02,260 --> 00:04:03,020
Nian.

66
00:04:03,410 --> 00:04:04,990
You really have no shame.

67
00:04:08,790 --> 00:04:10,020
Gu Nian, it hurts. It hurts!

68
00:04:13,390 --> 00:04:15,820
Let go, let go, let go!

69
00:04:16,500 --> 00:04:17,700
It really hurts!

70
00:04:17,860 --> 00:04:18,500
Su Yin.

71
00:04:18,860 --> 00:04:20,230
Can you stop being so childish?

72
00:04:20,290 --> 00:04:21,649
I have to destroy him with everything I've got,

73
00:04:21,649 --> 00:04:22,860
or he'll destroy you in the future.

74
00:04:24,100 --> 00:04:24,780
Yes.

75
00:04:25,300 --> 00:04:26,810
Now you're ruining me.

76
00:04:27,180 --> 00:04:28,790
You've vented your frustration, feeling better now?

77
00:04:28,990 --> 00:04:30,070
Did you ever think about me?

78
00:04:30,500 --> 00:04:31,420
How am I supposed to explain this to my mom,

79
00:04:31,460 --> 00:04:32,980
Uncle Wang, and Grandpa Meng?

80
00:04:33,620 --> 00:04:34,980
Can't you just leave this place

81
00:04:34,980 --> 00:04:36,140
or go back to school before doing this?

82
00:04:36,260 --> 00:04:37,020
No way.

83
00:04:37,460 --> 00:04:39,700
Feng Huanan is fooling all of you.

84
00:04:39,890 --> 00:04:41,500
And he was so self-righteous.

85
00:04:41,909 --> 00:04:43,460
I almost exhausted myself explaining to the professor today

86
00:04:43,460 --> 00:04:44,310
just to barely get out of it.

87
00:04:44,420 --> 00:04:45,260
As soon as I rushed over here,

88
00:04:45,260 --> 00:04:46,860
I found everyone talking about Feng Huanan.

89
00:04:46,860 --> 00:04:48,930
Even the security guards knew that Grandpa Meng had taken a liking to him.

90
00:04:49,220 --> 00:04:51,060
I asked around and found out you were the one who helped him.

91
00:04:51,170 --> 00:04:52,500
I wanted to ask you for clarification,

92
00:04:52,580 --> 00:04:53,580
but as soon as I entered the makeup room,

93
00:04:53,600 --> 00:04:55,480
I saw Feng Huanan begging Lyu Tu to forgive him.

94
00:04:55,510 --> 00:04:56,880
He said Lyu Tu was his first woman

95
00:04:56,900 --> 00:04:58,300
and that you were the one who seduced him.

96
00:04:59,100 --> 00:05:00,340
Do you know what you're saying?

97
00:05:01,780 --> 00:05:03,150
Tu would never do something like that.

98
00:05:03,500 --> 00:05:05,260
She would never betray me like that.

99
00:05:05,590 --> 00:05:06,060
Yes.

100
00:05:06,660 --> 00:05:08,050
Lyu Tu wasn't intentional.

101
00:05:08,270 --> 00:05:10,020
She was another victim of the lies,

102
00:05:10,630 --> 00:05:11,860
so nothing really changed.

103
00:05:12,390 --> 00:05:14,500
I thought everything was over.

104
00:05:14,520 --> 00:05:15,690
That's why I left with peace of mind.

105
00:05:15,790 --> 00:05:16,820
But in the end, Feng Huanan

106
00:05:16,820 --> 00:05:17,940
still made you fall in love with him,

107
00:05:18,110 --> 00:05:19,100
made you help him,

108
00:05:19,170 --> 00:05:20,650
and made you his mistress.

109
00:05:21,020 --> 00:05:22,580
No, Lyu Tu is the mistress.

110
00:05:22,720 --> 00:05:24,160
He has a fiancée at home.

111
00:05:24,230 --> 00:05:26,280
Gu Nian, we're the fourth party here.

112
00:05:26,740 --> 00:05:27,670
Can you shut up?

113
00:05:29,660 --> 00:05:30,380
I'm sorry.

114
00:05:30,940 --> 00:05:31,820
My dear self,

115
00:05:32,130 --> 00:05:33,330
I was negligent.

116
00:05:33,750 --> 00:05:34,950
I let you get hurt.

117
00:05:35,659 --> 00:05:36,820
I totally understand your pain.

118
00:05:37,370 --> 00:05:38,230
The pain I would feel seven years later

119
00:05:38,230 --> 00:05:39,300
is no less than what you're feeling now.

120
00:05:40,250 --> 00:05:41,650
You don't understand at all.

121
00:05:42,700 --> 00:05:43,659
You always think

122
00:05:43,980 --> 00:05:45,180
you're saving me.

123
00:05:45,590 --> 00:05:46,300
But it's you

124
00:05:47,420 --> 00:05:49,900
who has step by step

125
00:05:49,900 --> 00:05:51,940
shattered all the beauty in my life.

126
00:05:52,190 --> 00:05:54,020
Self-deception won't save you, Gu Nian.

127
00:05:54,460 --> 00:05:56,270
You think I care about Feng Huanan?

128
00:05:57,280 --> 00:05:58,360
Then you're wrong.

129
00:05:59,140 --> 00:06:00,790
I, Gu Nian, have always been someone

130
00:06:00,790 --> 00:06:02,110
who can let go when needed.

131
00:06:03,780 --> 00:06:04,740
I know.

132
00:06:06,550 --> 00:06:08,270
Whether it's now or seven years later,

133
00:06:08,860 --> 00:06:10,470
the one we care about the most is Lyu Tu.

134
00:06:11,840 --> 00:06:13,160
Although she's also a victim,

135
00:06:13,620 --> 00:06:14,750
I really can't accept

136
00:06:14,750 --> 00:06:16,420
her being with Feng Huanan.

137
00:06:18,740 --> 00:06:20,380
Instead of wasting time arguing with me here,

138
00:06:21,350 --> 00:06:23,670
why don't you go ask Tu yourself and get it straight?

139
00:06:23,900 --> 00:06:24,430
I...

140
00:06:26,640 --> 00:06:27,450
Gu Nian.

141
00:06:30,170 --> 00:06:30,920
You've changed.

142
00:06:37,800 --> 00:06:38,600
Gu Nian.

143
00:06:45,930 --> 00:06:48,250
Have I... have I changed?

144
00:06:54,340 --> 00:06:55,060
Be careful.

145
00:06:57,500 --> 00:06:58,580
Everything's packed, right?

146
00:06:58,700 --> 00:06:59,340
It's all packed.

147
00:07:02,680 --> 00:07:03,240
Come on.

148
00:07:10,500 --> 00:07:12,540
Alright, these things are all packed up too.

149
00:07:13,000 --> 00:07:14,960
Gu Nian, I'll give you a ride.

150
00:07:15,610 --> 00:07:16,410
No. You guys go ahead.

151
00:07:16,670 --> 00:07:18,100
Alright, we're leaving then.

152
00:07:36,020 --> 00:07:36,830
Where are you?

153
00:07:51,800 --> 00:07:55,360
I just saw you downstairs, and I opened it for you.

154
00:08:06,580 --> 00:08:07,580
If you had told me earlier

155
00:08:07,580 --> 00:08:09,510
that you and Feng Huanan were already in a relationship,

156
00:08:09,510 --> 00:08:10,740
I honestly wouldn't have cared.

157
00:08:11,170 --> 00:08:12,560
Why did you hide it from me?

158
00:08:15,860 --> 00:08:18,100
I didn't mean to hide it from you.

159
00:08:19,580 --> 00:08:20,820
I just couldn't find

160
00:08:20,820 --> 00:08:22,660
the right time to tell you.

161
00:08:23,660 --> 00:08:24,980
He's your idol.

162
00:08:25,140 --> 00:08:27,810
I was afraid you'd scold me when you found out

163
00:08:28,100 --> 00:08:28,980
he ended up with me.

164
00:08:29,220 --> 00:08:30,090
What would I scold you for?

165
00:08:30,900 --> 00:08:32,419
That you're not worthy? Or that he's not worthy?

166
00:08:32,860 --> 00:08:34,370
Tu, how long have we known each other?

167
00:08:34,659 --> 00:08:36,700
You know I care about you, not him.

168
00:08:36,970 --> 00:08:38,640
You should scold me!

169
00:08:39,190 --> 00:08:41,039
You should say, "Lyu Tu, you deserve this!"

170
00:08:45,780 --> 00:08:47,300
You do deserve it.

171
00:08:47,650 --> 00:08:50,020
Taking me to make chocolates was your idea, right?

172
00:08:50,910 --> 00:08:51,870
If I'm not mistaken,

173
00:08:51,900 --> 00:08:53,050
you paid for it too, right?

174
00:08:58,930 --> 00:09:00,130
I just remembered,

175
00:09:00,420 --> 00:09:02,020
he also gave me a silk scarf.

176
00:09:02,430 --> 00:09:04,060
Now that I think about it, that scarf

177
00:09:04,500 --> 00:09:05,860
probably wasn't from him either.

178
00:09:14,830 --> 00:09:16,000
It was indeed from me.

179
00:09:18,200 --> 00:09:20,960
He said he wanted to thank Uncle Wang.

180
00:09:21,030 --> 00:09:22,820
How could I let him pay?

181
00:09:23,700 --> 00:09:25,380
But Uncle Wang didn't want it at all.

182
00:09:26,070 --> 00:09:27,390
Why don't you take it back?

183
00:09:29,770 --> 00:09:30,770
First come, first served.

184
00:09:31,090 --> 00:09:31,730
It's yours now.

185
00:09:32,970 --> 00:09:35,590
I don't want this dirty thing he gave me.

186
00:09:36,670 --> 00:09:37,660
But I bought it after all.

187
00:09:37,660 --> 00:09:38,780
It's not exactly dirty.

188
00:09:39,020 --> 00:09:40,300
He touched it.

189
00:09:40,300 --> 00:09:41,500
Doesn't that make it dirty?

190
00:09:41,500 --> 00:09:42,460
I don't want it.

191
00:09:43,540 --> 00:09:45,420
Fine, we both won't take it.

192
00:09:47,430 --> 00:09:47,870
No,

193
00:09:47,870 --> 00:09:49,430
I just don't get it.

194
00:09:49,580 --> 00:09:51,020
I've never been in a relationship,

195
00:09:51,020 --> 00:09:52,270
and I guess I was just misled,

196
00:09:52,270 --> 00:09:53,540
but you?

197
00:09:54,590 --> 00:09:56,180
Extremes meet, maybe.

198
00:09:57,790 --> 00:09:58,870
If some random guy

199
00:09:58,870 --> 00:10:00,020
told me

200
00:10:00,020 --> 00:10:01,220
he'd take responsibility for me,

201
00:10:01,220 --> 00:10:02,540
I'd laugh

202
00:10:02,540 --> 00:10:04,220
and ignore him.

203
00:10:04,510 --> 00:10:05,830
But why did I take him seriously

204
00:10:06,520 --> 00:10:08,040
when he said it to me?

205
00:10:08,750 --> 00:10:11,120
I really… I'm such a fool.

206
00:10:11,150 --> 00:10:13,030
My brain must have been kicked by a donkey.

207
00:10:13,050 --> 00:10:14,370
I can't believe I fell for it.

208
00:10:18,690 --> 00:10:19,810
I see it now.

209
00:10:20,060 --> 00:10:21,300
The alcohol

210
00:10:21,300 --> 00:10:22,820
is ruining your head.

211
00:10:27,460 --> 00:10:29,470
I really feel so sorry for you.

212
00:10:30,580 --> 00:10:31,620
I'll drink this to punish myself.

213
00:10:32,460 --> 00:10:33,260
Don't drink anymore.

214
00:10:33,700 --> 00:10:35,380
You'll only make things worse.

215
00:10:37,220 --> 00:10:38,180
I'm going out for a bit.

216
00:10:38,300 --> 00:10:39,470
Where are you going?

217
00:10:46,570 --> 00:10:47,360
Throwing out the trash.

218
00:10:49,270 --> 00:10:50,180
Don't wait for me.

219
00:10:50,300 --> 00:10:51,420
It's so late...

220
00:10:52,110 --> 00:10:52,910
Nian.

221
00:11:15,700 --> 00:11:16,290
Thank you.

222
00:11:25,620 --> 00:11:27,420
Are you avoiding calling her,

223
00:11:27,800 --> 00:11:29,180
or are you waiting for her to call you?

224
00:11:30,310 --> 00:11:31,660
Which one do you think is more likely?

225
00:11:35,060 --> 00:11:35,860
Neither is likely.

226
00:11:37,300 --> 00:11:39,230
You still don't know yourself, do you?

227
00:11:39,360 --> 00:11:41,950
When you're falling apart, you just want to hide away,

228
00:11:42,320 --> 00:11:43,760
wishing the whole world

229
00:11:43,790 --> 00:11:44,580
couldn't find you.

230
00:11:45,460 --> 00:11:46,620
Give her some time.

231
00:11:47,820 --> 00:11:48,740
She'll figure it out.

232
00:11:49,300 --> 00:11:51,180
I thought I could change the ending completely,

233
00:11:52,310 --> 00:11:53,650
but after going around in circles,

234
00:11:53,980 --> 00:11:55,220
it feels like it's all come back to the same point.

235
00:11:56,580 --> 00:11:58,260
Everything I've done was for her.

236
00:12:00,950 --> 00:12:02,910
But when I saw her break down today,

237
00:12:03,510 --> 00:12:05,760
I felt so heartbroken, so very heartbroken.

238
00:12:08,130 --> 00:12:09,420
After all, she is me.

239
00:12:12,500 --> 00:12:13,420
You're not wrong.

240
00:12:14,460 --> 00:12:17,100
But you can't stop her from walking her own path

241
00:12:17,380 --> 00:12:18,890
just to keep her from making mistakes.

242
00:12:19,620 --> 00:12:21,340
Sometimes, facing painful truths

243
00:12:21,530 --> 00:12:22,730
is the real growth.

244
00:12:25,220 --> 00:12:26,610
So you mean,

245
00:12:27,430 --> 00:12:29,070
the only way the ending can change

246
00:12:29,920 --> 00:12:31,490
is if she grows on her own?

247
00:12:39,630 --> 00:12:40,460
I don't know.

248
00:12:41,660 --> 00:12:42,740
I just think

249
00:12:43,250 --> 00:12:44,380
no matter what you do,

250
00:12:45,060 --> 00:12:46,740
she will always have to face the storm alone.

251
00:12:51,340 --> 00:12:52,750
What she needs isn't a cage,

252
00:12:53,180 --> 00:12:53,980
but armor.

253
00:12:54,700 --> 00:12:56,570
You can't walk this road with her forever.

254
00:12:57,740 --> 00:12:58,420
After all,

255
00:12:59,780 --> 00:13:01,190
you don't belong to this time and space.

256
00:13:04,340 --> 00:13:05,020
Gu Nian.

257
00:13:05,340 --> 00:13:06,500
What do you want from me?

258
00:13:06,530 --> 00:13:07,970
I'm of no use to you anymore.

259
00:13:08,420 --> 00:13:08,980
No.

260
00:13:09,040 --> 00:13:09,940
After you left,

261
00:13:10,140 --> 00:13:10,820
you never came back.

262
00:13:10,820 --> 00:13:11,780
I've been so worried about you.

263
00:13:12,940 --> 00:13:14,260
Don't play the emotional card.

264
00:13:14,340 --> 00:13:15,980
It used to work, but not anymore.

265
00:13:16,300 --> 00:13:17,740
I'm not trying to play an emotional card.

266
00:13:17,740 --> 00:13:18,660
I just think

267
00:13:18,660 --> 00:13:20,670
it's necessary to make things clear with you.

268
00:13:21,020 --> 00:13:22,820
For work-related things, just talk to Uncle Wang directly.

269
00:13:22,820 --> 00:13:23,760
You don't need to go through me.

270
00:13:23,780 --> 00:13:25,460
About you and Lyu Tu, talk to her.

271
00:13:25,860 --> 00:13:27,420
I don't know about your fiancée.

272
00:13:27,830 --> 00:13:28,820
As for us,

273
00:13:29,730 --> 00:13:30,370
it's over.

274
00:13:34,500 --> 00:13:35,020
Gu Nian.

275
00:13:35,430 --> 00:13:36,020
Gu Nian!

276
00:13:37,830 --> 00:13:38,860
Can't you just give me one more chance

277
00:13:38,860 --> 00:13:40,180
to explain things to you?

278
00:13:56,110 --> 00:13:57,100
